description:
A skirmish wargame of prehistoric survival.

Hide, Stone, and Bone is a wargame of hunting and combat in which players lead tribes of early human ancestors as they attempt to survive in the face of the perils of the Ice Age. From season to season, tribes seek to grow and prosper, engaging in various 'Big Days' that represent important events such as mammoth hunts, attacks by cave bears, and clashes with rival tribes. In between these encounters, tribes must gather food, craft tools and weapons, and consult their shamans to prepare themselves for the next threat, be it from enemies, animals, nature, or something stranger&hellip;

While the skirmishes and hunts of Big Days are resolved using a d10-based alternating activation system, Hide, Stone, and Bone also features a detailed campaign system that forms a core part of the gameplay experience. Ultimately, survival is all &ndash; defeating other tribes is not the sole focus and it is possible for tribes to thrive even if the fortunes of war are against them. With options for solo, cooperative, and competitive play, Hide, Stone, and Bone gives players all the tools they need to meet the challenges of the Ice Age and lead their tribes into a prosperous future.

Players must outbid each other with the highest-numbered card to be the first to get rid of all their cards. But it's not quite that simple: The character cards with their special abilities really shake things up! Immerse yourself in the world of Lucifer and his companions with this fast-paced, strategic card game.

&bull;&bull;&bull;

Spieler m&uuml;ssen sich gegenseitig mit der h&ouml;chsten Zahlenkarte &uuml;berbieten, um als erste alle Karten loszuwerden. Doch ganz so einfach ist es nicht: Die Charakterkarten mit ihren Spezialf&auml;higkeiten mischen das Spiel ordentlich auf! Taucht mit diesem schnellen, strategischen Kartenspiel in die Welt von Luzifer und seinen Gef&auml;hrten ein.

&ldquo;These board game personalities are hungry after a long day gaming! Can you serve all of them their orders?&rdquo;

This promotional pack of order cards features new orders from some friendly faces; board game personalities with their favourite sandwiches! Replace your regular order cards with this promotional pack for more variety in your games.

Profits from the sale of this product will be split equally and donated to The Trussel Trust UK and No Child Left Hungry US.

Where you looking for the perfect drinking game? Shoots Wengue is a motor skill game, in which you have to fit it the rings into a hook, if you accomplish it you have to advance the shot of whatever beverage or cocktail you&acute;re playing with, to your opponents side. If it reaches either yours or your opponent&acute;s end, that player has to drink the beverage. The more you play the harder it is to fit in the rings.

&bull;&bull;&bull;

&iquest;Buscas un juego para tomar? Shoots Wengue es un juego de destreza en donde tienes que encajar los aros, si lo logras vas a hacer que tu oponente tome.

Are you ready to take a ride in the most used transport services by the Bogotans? In this frantic game, you are a civil living in Bogota and you&acute;re trying to travel all around the city. Pay your ticket to enter into the most massive transportation system in Bogot&aacute;. Throw the dice and advance through the city in order to accomplish the most objectives and then return to your home before your opponents do it so you can win your game.

&bull;&bull;&bull;

&iquest;Est&aacute;s listo para conocer el medio de transporte m&aacute;s usado por los bogotanos? En este alocado juego, eres un transe&uacute;nte que quiere hacer viajes por toda la metr&oacute;polis de Colombia. Paga tu pasaje para ingresar al sistema de transporte m&aacute;s masivo de Bogot&aacute;. Viaja por la ciudad para conseguir tus objetivos privados y regresa a tu hogar antes que los dem&aacute;s jugadores.

In this mine the cards are falling. Minero loco is a fun game where players turn by turn will be placing cards in front of them to mine the most treasures. Draw a card and then play a card, some cards may also collapse your opponents mine or even yours, look out for that. When none of the players can draw cards, the game end and the player with the most amount of mined treasures will be the winner.

&bull;&bull;&bull;

En esta mina se caen las cartas. Minero loco es un divertido juego d&oacute;nde los jugadores van a ir colocando cartas para armar la mejor mina de oro, colecciona tesoros y genera derrumbes en la mina de tus oponentes. El jugador con mayor cantidad de tesoros ser&aacute; el ganador del juego.

It is a mini-expantion made to commemorate the release of the Korean version of the Codename, and consists of 10 animal cards (20 words) in a compound word.

&bull;&bull;&bull;

코드네임의 한국어판 출시를 기념해 제작된 미니 획장으로, 합성어로 된 동물 카드 10장(20 단어)으로 구성되어 있습니다.

Mueve y Busca is a play-at-home game where each child needs their own plush toy or amigurumi&mdash;because their toy becomes the main character. The game offers two play modes (Move and Search) designed to turn everyday spaces into a playful adventure, mixing imagination with movement and exploration.

In the Move mode, you shuffle 27 cards and spread them face down on the table. The deck is divided into three types: Body Parts, Actions, and Things Around the House. On each turn, you flip three cards (one from each type) and everyone completes the challenge at the same time: take your toy to the place/object shown, holding it the way the body-part card indicates and performing the action shown. For example, you might need to carry your toy to a chair, holding it with two fingers while hopping on one foot. It&rsquo;s easy to learn, but hilarious to play.

The first player to finish wins the round and keeps the cards. The game ends when the cards run out, and the player with the most cards wins. Along the way, kids naturally practice coordination, gross motor skills, focus, and creativity, without it ever feeling like &ldquo;learning.&rdquo;

Эволюция волшебных тварей: Подарочный набор ("Evolution: Another World &ndash; Gift Set") is a gift set that includes:


     Evolution: Another World core game;
     components for 5th and 6th player: Rare Species;
     an automated opponent: Gnasher;
     Price of Power module;
     Aethereal Beings module.


Note: This set includes fewer components than Evolution: Another World – Special Edition, and only in Russian.

The alien invasion has begun, and humans are in a rush to escape Earth before it&rsquo;s too late! The only problem is that aliens are disguised as humans! Our only hope is to weed out the aliens via the power of &hellip; multiple choice questions!

While the aliens know how to blend in and look like us, they don&rsquo;t quite understand human culture. These questions are carefully crafted to help expose the space invaders. All you have to do is answer like any normal human would. It&rsquo;s that easy! It&rsquo;s only the fate of humanity at stake &hellip; Don&rsquo;t sweat it!

In Totally Human, players are given hidden identities (human or alien) and must answer three multiple-choice questions as "human-like" as possible, but aliens don't understand human culture completely and face restrictions on how they can respond.&nbsp;

The humans&rsquo; goal is to escape on the biggest alien-free rocket to form a new colony out in the stars.&nbsp;

The aliens&rsquo; goal is to blend in and sneak onto any rocket with humans for a tasty, post-invasion snack.&nbsp;

Both aliens and humans can achieve their goals on different rockets, but it's also possible that nobody wins. Be careful who you trust!

&mdash;description from the publisher

Imagine that the boundaries of time have dissolved, and outstanding Belarusians from different eras have found themselves in the 21st century. What did they see and how did they react? How did they apply their talents and reveal their character? All of this will be up to you to decide! Yet time plays cruel tricks, and some Characters have acquired doubles who must be urgently discovered. Or perhaps the double is you? How can you avoid giving yourself away when your nature urges you to act as usual&hellip;

In the board game Tuteishiya, you will take on the role of a famous Belarusian, answering tricky questions while trying to figure out which of the players is your double. The game features 50 remarkable Belarusians from different times, and you will have the chance to step into the role of each one.

Additionally, Tuteishiya can be played according to the rules of the well‑known game Who am I!

Ziffernwald is a roll‑and‑write game where, round after round, you compete to harvest the best batch of numbers and score points accordingly.
Each round, you move through the forest based on a die roll and then compare your harvest. And every round, the magical forest changes your harvesting goal. Sometimes you want the lowest total, sometimes the highest, sometimes only even digits, and sometimes something completely different &hellip;
Not so easy to find your way through this thicket of numbers!

Explore the mysteries of Venice and the forgotten art of alchemy with this supplement for The Silver Bayonet, featuring solo and competitive campaigns, new soldiers, and new enemies.

Though the years of Austrian occupation and repression have ended and Venice is back in French hands, fear still hangs heavy over the City of Masks. Rumours abound, telling of strange figures leaping across rooftops, of monsters out in the lagoon, of bodies bearing mysterious wounds pulled from the canals. The people whisper of the brutal Venetian Civic Guard, of the raids on bookshops and libraries, of the arrests of scientists and physicians, and wonder what they could possibly be seeking with such fervour&hellip; and whose agenda they serve.

This is the Venice into which you are sent, charged with navigating the occult underworld of the city to acquire grimoires and relics amassed by Venetian collectors over the centuries. Two campaigns, one solo and one competitive, will test your resolve &ndash; for despite the new recruits at your disposal and the alchemical arsenal that can be fielded, you must face the muskets of rival factions, the menace of terrifying creatures, and the machinations of a hidden power&hellip;

You're a captain whose ambition is bigger than your purse. After finally getting your hands on a rickety ship, you start at the tavern&mdash;enjoy a drink and recruit a crew of fellow spirits. Then, it's time to set sail! Your goal is simple: get rich. But the sea never gives without taking; unknown dangers are waiting&hellip;

Captain Keep Upright is a 2&ndash;5 player tabletop game of Set Collection and Push Your Luck. Play takes place over 5 rounds, each split into a Recruitment Phase and a Voyage Phase. Use Closed Drafting to pick the crew you need&mdash;collecting sets of the same or different types will bring you various rewards. Once all players have drafted, the Voyage Phase begins: keep drawing cards from the voyage deck. The more treasure chests you reveal, the better the loot you can claim&mdash;but sailing is never safe. A shipwreck could leave you with nothing, so deciding whether to press your luck or play it safe is everything. Don't worry, though: use your crew's abilities wisely, and they might just save the day when it matters most. Outmaneuver your rivals and seize the legendary treasure!

&mdash;description from the designer

Discovery Curiosidades has six different themes. Each one with almost 500 questions. The themes are: 

    human body and health;
    culture and history of humanity;
    fauna and flora;
    geography;
    technology;
    varieties;


What did you discover today? Discover unbelievable things! Some questions are quite difficult, others very easy, and some answers are even absurd and funny. This balance was designed to allow the Discovery game to be played by people of different ages and knowledge levels, providing pleasant moments of great fun and culture, and of course, some good laughs... The objective of each player is to score the highest number of positive points in the greatest possible number of themes and rounds.
